{"key":"post-12588163","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12588163</id>\n<content>Don't use tap water for spore syringes.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Distilled is best.&amp;nbsp; Tap water is fine for growing mushrooms once spores have germinated, but spores and chlorine don't mix well.&amp;nbsp; If you have a well, you can use that for syringes after filtering.&amp;nbsp; If not, the minerals in well water tend to cause the spores to germinate in the syringes.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12588198</next>\n<prev>12587771</prev>\n<first>12587534</first>\n<last>18788854</last>\n<when>1274232980</when>\n<utime>05/19/10 04:36 AM</utime>\n</post>"}